Rating: 3
I modified this a bit. first of all, i decided to roast the broccoli, though in the process of doing this i found a new technique. I had preheated the oven to 425 and just popped in the broccoli (1 whole head) when i had to unexpectedly leave the house. So, i simply turned off the oven and left in the broccoli, expecting to roast it later. Well, when I got home the broccoli was completely cooked and absolutely delicious. The texture was almost chewy and the flavor was very concentrated with no extra salt added. I think i must had dried it or somehting, but it's delicious this way, not to mention energy saving. Anyway, the rest of the recipe is the same except halved the butter, added a bit of evoo, and a touch of lemon juice. Next time I might also add some hot chili flakes. very tastey and simple.

