Rating: 4
I made this for a crowd and doubled everything in the recipe except for the butter (two sticks just seemed obscene), and it came out great. I used "domestic" butter, as that's what I had on hand. I used fresh basil and Italian parsley from my garden, and yum, what a delight. This gets four forks because not only is it delicious, but it uses simple, fresh ingredients, and it is a snap to prepare. I might try adding even more broccoli next time, and perhaps throw some red pepper strips in to boot--would make a beautiful presentation. My daughter's friends tried squeezing some fresh lemon juice on theirs, which sounded like a good idea, but I tried it and liked it better without. Don't skip the parmesan cheese!

